it wasnt directed at me, but i believe i can elaborate on that sentiment...<br>
<br>
not necessarily legalize drugs, but to decriminalize small quantities(i wouldnet assume to define what small quantity would be, prob different for each type of drug) would inevitably lead to a better prison system that would cost taxpayers much less money. which would in turn decrease crime and possibly lead to more children having both parents in their lives. taxing the decriminalized drugs would lead to revenues that could be either dumped into the schools as someone else said, or used to provide rehab services, etc. i know these are broad statements, but it isnt hard to see how the decriminalization of drug use would benefit our society.  <p>&quot;i think the good book is missing some pages&quot;<br>
