<br>
Decriminalizing marijuana is advocated even by ultra-conservatives like William F. Buckley and would surely get us out of some rather ridiculous political situations (can you say Noriega?) not to mention force us to deal with the REAL causes of drug addiction in this country. <br>
<br>
Unfortuneately, throwing everyone in jail and characterizing drug dealers as the worse scum of the earth-below murderers and rapists appeals to the sheeple masses out there who want a fast, easy solution and don't bother to notice that this &quot;War&quot; has been neither.<br>
<br>
P.S. I keep hearing the right say if we legalize drugs everyone will be running around with needles in their arms but I can tell you the reason I don't use heroine has NOTHING to do with it's being illegal and I never like pot, but see nothing wrong with that either if used in moderation (just like beer). Smoking kills more people than every single narcotic put together each year, but how are we attacking that? Public health messages and making it uncool. <br>
<br>
P.S.S.--those commercials about supporting terrorism with drug money could be used to say exactly the SAME things about our tax dollars. They are stupid and pander only to those who know nothing about addiction.<br>
